HEADWORD: Dynastidan
<hw>Dy*nas"ti*dan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fem.
of <?/. See <er>Dynast</er>. The name alludes to the immense size of
some species.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a group of gigantic,
horned beetles, including <spn>Dynastus Neptunus</spn>, and the
<stype>Hercules beetle</stype> (<spn>Dynastus Hercules</spn>) of
tropical America, which grow to be six inches in length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

